00:49.897 --> 00:51.472
Tell me, seer,

00:51.506 --> 00:55.085
What do I hold
in my hand now?

00:55.120 --> 00:56.560
shh.

00:56.594 --> 00:58.534
You're holding...

01:00.310 --> 01:01.746
A wallet.

01:01.781 --> 01:04.691
Yes! Incredible.
Ten out of ten.

01:04.726 --> 01:06.231
What's going on?

01:06.266 --> 01:07.577
Gram's teaching me
how to read minds.

01:07.978 --> 01:09.478
And she is a natural.

01:09.611 --> 01:10.954
Much better than you were
at her age.

01:10.955 --> 01:11.955
And I'm very proud.

01:12.488 --> 01:14.896
Why the sudden foray
into the mysterious realms?

01:14.930 --> 01:17.637
It's a genealogy project for
school. Half of the assignment

01:17.673 --> 01:19.610
is to collect stories
from family members.

01:19.644 --> 01:21.582
I had no idea
that gram's folks

01:21.617 --> 01:23.527
had a mind-reading act
on Coney Island.

01:23.528 --> 01:25.328
Yeah, they were
very famous in their day.

01:25.761 --> 01:27.633
I love all their codes--
how "tell me" means wallet

01:27.667 --> 01:30.475
and "reveal to me"
means a pair of glasses.

01:30.509 --> 01:32.447
Yes, you come from
a long line

01:32.481 --> 01:34.352
of hucksters and charlatans,
myself included.

01:34.386 --> 01:36.391
But we have high hopes
for you.

01:38.430 --> 01:40.400
That must be Beckett.

01:40.435 --> 01:42.072
How did you know?

01:42.106 --> 01:45.012
It's after 10:00
on a weekday.

01:45.047 --> 01:46.950
Who else is it gonna be?

01:46.985 --> 01:48.424
Oh, she is good.

01:49.025 --> 01:50.025
Brilliant.

01:50.058 --> 01:51.360
Castle.

01:51.395 --> 01:53.165
I knew it was you.

01:53.199 --> 01:55.203
Victim is
a hispanic male, mid-30s.

01:55.237 --> 01:58.243
A local spotted him
when he was out walking s dog,

01:58.277 --> 01:59.980
around 10:30.

02:00.014 --> 02:01.917
His wallet's missing.
If it was a robbery,

02:01.952 --> 02:05.057
I bet my week's salary that the killer
didn't know who he was rolling.

02:05.091 --> 02:07.395
You I.D.'ed him
without a wallet?

02:07.430 --> 02:09.466
Unfortunately.
You know the guy?

02:09.501 --> 02:12.172
Everybody in New York
knows the guy.

02:12.207 --> 02:14.743
Cano Vega,
the baseball player.

02:15.078 --> 02:17.081
Yep.
Cano Vega?
Are you sure?

02:17.115 --> 02:18.284
He was
my first-round draft pick

02:18.319 --> 02:19.957
in my fantasy league
three years running.

02:20.391 --> 02:24.496
.314 batting average,
4 gold gloves, and one...

02:25.330 --> 02:27.200
championship ring.

02:27.234 --> 02:29.604
I almost caught one of
his homers once.

02:29.639 --> 02:30.942
He had just came
to the states from Cuba,

02:31.076 --> 02:33.483
and my dad took us out
to the bleachers over at Shea.

02:33.484 --> 02:34.784
I didn't know
you were a baseball fan.

02:34.817 --> 02:36.953
It's genetic,
on my dad's side.

02:37.488 --> 02:39.360
Been taking me to games
since I was 3.

02:39.361 --> 02:40.761
Yeah, mine, too.

02:41.395 --> 02:43.264
What about you, Castle?

02:43.298 --> 02:44.301
Your dad a baseball fan?

02:44.435 --> 02:45.540
I really can't say.

02:45.541 --> 02:47.341
Castle is
famously fatherless.

02:47.774 --> 02:48.544
What, are you adopted
or something?

02:48.545 --> 02:49.345
No.

02:49.379 --> 02:51.581
Then how do you--
it's complicated.

02:51.616 --> 02:53.017
It's not <i>that</i> complicated.

02:53.052 --> 02:54.789
Someone used his head
for batting practice.

02:55.123 --> 02:57.191
36-ouncer to the back
of the head.

02:57.225 --> 02:59.429
By the look of the spatter,
he was hit multiple times.

02:59.430 --> 03:00.430
Time of death?

03:00.564 --> 03:02.867
Uh, from his temperature,
I'd say two,

03:02.902 --> 03:04.439
maybe three hour
at the most.

03:04.540 --> 03:05.740
What's with
all this bruising?

03:06.274 --> 03:07.747
Postmortem,
from the balls.

03:07.848 --> 03:10.548
Pitching arm--it ran
for a while after he was dead.

03:10.881 --> 03:12.616
So you'd think a guy
like Cano Vega

03:12.651 --> 03:14.754
would have a batting cage
in his basement.

03:15.188 --> 03:17.824
What would he be doing
in a sketchy neighborhood

03:17.858 --> 03:20.495
in Spanish Harlem
at this hour of the night?

03:20.830 --> 03:23.099
Maybe because
it's Cano Vega Field.

03:23.133 --> 03:25.536
Local uniforms said that
he built it for the community,

03:25.570 --> 03:27.205
wanted to
give something back.

03:27.240 --> 03:28.908
So our killer

03:28.943 --> 03:31.345
hit him from here.

03:31.379 --> 03:34.016
And he got blood
on his shoe.

03:34.050 --> 03:35.953
Have C.S.U. run a sweep.

03:35.987 --> 03:36.458
See if anything tracked
outside of the field.

03:36.459 --> 03:37.459
All right.

03:37.992 --> 03:42.329
So your dad, what is it,
a "Mamma Mia!" thing?

03:42.364 --> 03:44.366
Early '70s, free love.

03:44.400 --> 03:46.537
Yeah, I'll bet your mom was
kinda wild back in the day.

03:46.572 --> 03:48.110
You really need
to stop talking now.

03:48.211 --> 03:49.511
Sorry. Done.

03:54.015 --> 03:55.182
A big, athletic guy

03:55.217 --> 03:58.287
is swinging
a 2-1/2-foot club.

03:58.321 --> 03:59.460
He couldn't have been
that easy to kill.

03:59.961 --> 04:01.661
Unless he didn't
see it coming.

04:02.294 --> 04:04.196
On behalf
of the Vega family...

04:04.230 --> 04:06.267
I want to thank
all of Cano's loyal fans

04:06.302 --> 04:08.304
for their love and support.

04:08.338 --> 04:10.507
In this time of great sadness,

04:10.541 --> 04:12.708
we ask that you please respect
his family's privacy.

04:12.709 --> 04:13.709
Mr. Fox who else is...

04:14.743 --> 04:16.276
12 years of marriage--

04:16.310 --> 04:17.877
All they want from me
is a sound bite.

04:17.911 --> 04:20.313
I'm very sorry
about your loss, Mrs. Vega.

04:20.346 --> 04:22.084
Do you know why he'd be
in the park last night?

04:22.885 --> 04:24.685
Sometimes he'd go there
to blow off steam,

04:25.218 --> 04:26.420
but never at night.

04:26.421 --> 04:28.021
Do you know where he was
earlier in the evening?

04:28.255 --> 04:29.622
He was at my club.

04:29.623 --> 04:30.623
Thanks.

04:31.057 --> 04:32.090
Detective Beckett,
Mr. Castle,

04:32.125 --> 04:33.859
Tommy Zane--
Cano's old teammate.

04:33.993 --> 04:35.127
Be hard to be a New Yorker
and not know

04:35.161 --> 04:36.463
Freight Train Tommy Zane.

04:36.564 --> 04:37.964
So you guys got any leads?

04:38.097 --> 04:39.934
We're looking into it.
Mr. Zane, you said

04:39.968 --> 04:42.103
that Mr. Vega was
at your club last night?

04:42.104 --> 04:43.304
Our club, actually.

04:43.437 --> 04:45.172
Cano and I owned it with
a couple of other players.

04:45.173 --> 04:46.173
Do you know about what time?

04:46.306 --> 04:48.874
Dropped by about 7:00.
Left about 7:30.

04:48.908 --> 04:50.243
I didn't really see him.
I was with a friend.

04:52.277 --> 04:54.378
Excuse me. Yeah.

04:54.413 --> 04:55.447
Mrs. Vega,
do you know of anyone

04:55.481 --> 04:57.016
who would've wanted
to hurt your husband?

04:57.117 --> 04:59.017
Used to be,
everybody loved him,

04:59.750 --> 05:01.518
Especially
in the Cuban community.

05:01.552 --> 05:02.587
What changed?

05:02.588 --> 05:03.588
The trip.

05:04.621 --> 05:05.955
A-a few months ago,

05:05.989 --> 05:08.090
the Cuban tourism department
approached him.

05:08.125 --> 05:10.893
They wanted Cano to be
the poster boy for the new Cuba.

05:10.961 --> 05:12.895
You risk your life
to escape Castro's Cuba,

05:12.930 --> 05:14.364
why would you
go back to visit?

05:14.398 --> 05:15.299
While Cano was down there,

05:15.333 --> 05:18.968
the locals treated him
like a hero--their hero.

05:19.203 --> 05:21.804
At a state dinner, Castro
came over and shook his hand.

05:21.939 --> 05:24.140
When he got home, his friends
called him a traitor for going,

05:24.175 --> 05:25.775
said he was
a lapdog for Fidel.

05:26.510 --> 05:28.412
The same people who cheered
when he built that ballpark

05:28.446 --> 05:29.614
came up and told him
to go to hell.

05:29.615 --> 05:30.615
Did he get any threats?

05:30.649 --> 05:33.751
You bet he got threats,
hundreds of them,

05:34.585 --> 05:37.420
and all of them
courtesy of Alfredo Quintana.

05:37.754 --> 05:39.557
Detective, Bobby Fox,
Cano's agent.

05:39.558 --> 05:40.558
Nice to meet you.

05:40.591 --> 05:42.626
Detective, could you do
something to get those jackals

05:42.660 --> 05:44.796
and their cameras
away from Mrs. Vega's house?

05:44.797 --> 05:45.797
I'll see what I can do.

05:46.130 --> 05:48.265
Thanks.
Who's Alfredo Quintana?

05:48.300 --> 05:50.635
He's the guy
who killed Cano Vega.

05:52.770 --> 05:53.870
Thanks, Carlos.

05:54.404 --> 05:56.272
Hey.

05:56.607 --> 05:58.207
Alfredo Quintana--

05:58.241 --> 06:01.940
J.D., Phd and editor
of "Una Nueva Esperanza,"

06:02.074 --> 06:04.175
a newspaper published by
his foundation,

06:04.209 --> 06:05.675
primarily
for the Cuban community.

06:05.809 --> 06:07.409
This is his column
from two weeks ago.

06:07.510 --> 06:09.310
"Cano Vega must pay"?

06:09.344 --> 06:11.644
The article's about how Vega
betrayed the Cuban community

06:11.678 --> 06:13.377
by shaking hands
with the monster

06:13.412 --> 06:15.045
who butchered thousands
of their relatives.

06:15.579 --> 06:17.645
Quintana says, "if Vega
is going to embrace

06:17.679 --> 06:20.044
"the brutal regime
he once escaped,

06:20.112 --> 06:24.146
he would do well to be reminded
of its barbarous cruelty."

06:24.180 --> 06:26.280
Well, that sounds
like a threat to me.

06:27.115 --> 06:28.080
I wasn't threatening him.

06:28.115 --> 06:31.948
You turned the local
Cuban community against him.

06:31.982 --> 06:33.281
He turned his back
on his people

06:33.315 --> 06:35.316
when he gave Castro
his nod of approval.

06:35.350 --> 06:38.218
If you want me to be sorry about
what I wrote because he's dead,

06:38.253 --> 06:39.753
I'm not.

06:39.787 --> 06:41.287
I wrote the truth.

06:41.322 --> 06:43.222
Are you sure
that's all you did?

06:43.257 --> 06:45.257
You said it yourself
in your editorial,

06:45.291 --> 06:46.692
Vega should pay.

06:46.726 --> 06:47.726
It's a free country,
isn't it?

06:49.461 --> 06:51.127
I'm entitled
to express my opinion.

06:51.162 --> 06:53.262
Your foundation--
Cubans First--

06:53.296 --> 06:55.198
is on East 98th Street.

06:55.632 --> 06:57.067
That's three blocks away

06:57.101 --> 06:59.402
from the field
where Vega's body was found.

06:59.436 --> 07:01.438
You think I had something
to do with his murder?

07:01.472 --> 07:03.740
Well, the pen is mightier
than the sword.

07:03.775 --> 07:06.042
But a baseball bat can be
pretty effective, too.

07:06.077 --> 07:08.445
Where were you last night
between 7:00 and 10:00 pm?

07:08.546 --> 07:10.246
I was at home with my wife.

07:10.279 --> 07:12.880
Mm. Wives make
such convenient alibis.

07:13.115 --> 07:14.549
My sons
were there as well...

07:15.784 --> 07:17.250
as well as my brother.

07:17.685 --> 07:18.286
Do you have anyone
who isn't blood related?

07:20.020 --> 07:21.621
A notary, perhaps?

07:22.156 --> 07:25.391
Look, what Cano Vega did
is inexcusable.

07:26.426 --> 07:28.660
But I am not a murderer.

07:28.694 --> 07:30.428
Are you sure about that,
Mr. Quintana?

07:30.563 --> 07:33.131
You incited an entire community
against him.

07:34.065 --> 07:35.565
So from where I'm standing,

07:35.599 --> 07:37.533
you might not have swung
that bat,

07:37.567 --> 07:40.402
but that doesn't mean
that you didn't kill him.

07:44.774 --> 07:46.074
Well?
We'll check his alibi...

07:46.075 --> 07:47.644
but my gut tells me
it's not him.

07:47.645 --> 07:49.145
We should get a warrant,
run his subscribers

07:49.178 --> 07:51.013
against any hate mail that
the Vegas might have gotten.

07:51.014 --> 07:53.214
You sure you got no cop
in the Castle family tree?

07:53.247 --> 07:53.947
No, us Castles

07:53.982 --> 07:55.749
are mostly con artists
and circus folk, sir.

07:55.784 --> 07:57.485
No, I think there's
a little cop in there somewhere.

08:00.420 --> 08:01.287
Con artists

08:01.321 --> 08:01.955
and circus people, huh?

08:02.089 --> 08:03.356
Yep, and mind readers.

08:03.390 --> 08:06.657
Really? So tell me
what I'm thinking.

08:06.692 --> 08:07.959
aah.

08:07.993 --> 08:10.693
You're... You're thinking...

08:10.727 --> 08:13.196
You don't care and you want me
to stop talking.

08:13.530 --> 08:15.297
Ooh, that's uncanny.

08:15.332 --> 08:16.199
It's in the blood.
Yo, Beckett.

08:16.234 --> 08:18.068
Yeah.
Just got back from C.S.U.

08:19.002 --> 08:21.070
They managed to track the blood
trail from the killer's shoe

08:21.103 --> 08:23.804
across the park.
It dead-ended at the curb.

08:23.939 --> 08:25.374
So our killer
was driving a car.

08:25.375 --> 08:26.775
Yeah. The area
was a little muddy,

08:26.808 --> 08:28.642
so we were able to pull
a partial on the tire.

08:28.643 --> 08:29.643
Any make and model?

08:29.877 --> 08:31.744
Better. The tire marks
are distinctive.

08:31.778 --> 08:33.044
They've been patched
in two spots.

08:33.179 --> 08:35.647
Now those same tire tracks
match a car that was tagged

08:35.682 --> 08:37.582
in an aggravated assault
last year.

08:37.616 --> 08:39.650
The asault was committed
with a baseball bat

08:39.684 --> 08:41.285
By one Anton Wade.

08:41.287 --> 08:43.287
Loan sharking, blackmail.

08:43.520 --> 08:46.253
Plus assault with
a deadly weapon and two A&B's--

08:46.487 --> 08:48.785
Assault and battery.
I know.

08:48.820 --> 08:50.788
Right. The guy's
one seriously bad dude.

08:50.822 --> 08:54.790
Whoa! Whoa, whoa, whoa. Oh,
I'm sensing something here--

08:54.825 --> 09:00.292
that... this guy
might just be our killer.

